On Mon, Jan 12, 2009 at 8:17 AM, Arnaud Bailly &lt;arnaud.oqube@...&gt;wrote:

&gt; Hello,
&gt; Following this list&#39;s advices, I have rewritten my forme JUnit3 tests
&gt; using JUnit 4. What I did was creating a subclass of Paramaterized
&gt; with a special annotation and a method load() that actually runs the
&gt; HtmlUnit tests, constructs the results and returns a collection of
&gt; JQTest that can later be used as parameters with Parameterized
&gt; annotaion.
&gt;
&gt; The abridged runner code is:
&gt;
&gt; public class JQUnitRunner extends Parameterized {
&gt;
&gt;  private static String testPagePath;
&gt;
&gt;  @Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
&gt;  public static @interface Page {
&gt;
&gt;    String value();
&gt;
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;  public JQUnitRunner(Class&lt;?&gt; clazz) throws Exception {
&gt;    super(clazz);
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;  public static class JQTest { ... }
&gt;
&gt;  private static HtmlUnitDriver driver;
&gt;  private static final String basedir = System.getProperty(&quot;basedir&quot;, &quot;.&quot;);
&gt;
&gt;  public static List&lt;JQTest[]&gt; load(Class&lt;?&gt; clazz) { ... }
&gt;
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; It is used by test class instances using the following idiom:
&gt;
&gt; @RunWith(JQUnitRunner.class)
&gt; @...(&quot;test-etatflash&quot;)
&gt; public class EtatFlashTest {
&gt;
&gt;  private JQTest jqTest;
&gt;
&gt;  @Parameters
&gt;  public static Collection&lt;JQTest[]&gt; jqtests() {
&gt;    return JQUnitRunner.load(EtatFlashTest.class);
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;  public EtatFlashTest(JQTest test) {
&gt;    this.jqTest = test;
&gt;  }
&gt;
&gt;  @Test
&gt;  public void test() {
&gt;    jqTest.assertPass();
&gt;  }
&gt; }
&gt;
&gt; I am not entirely satisfied with this, as there is still boilerplate
&gt; code in the test classes. I would have liked to override the following
&gt; method from Parameterized but it is private:
&gt;
&gt;        private List&lt;Object[]&gt; getParametersList(TestClass klass)
&gt;
&gt; Overriding would have allowed to remove entirely the jqtests method
&gt; from test classes.
&gt;
&gt; regards
&gt;
